Articles.Content:
I never had something like this before, everything was okay until the chute fully deployed.

It's a GameData\WildBlueIndustries\MOLE\Parts\Coupling\Mk1DockingPort.cfg on top of a BDB Gemini capsule.

Luckily I splashed down without issues - well, I was upside down but who cares...

Vid:

Log:
https://www.dropbox.com/s/omyv5vvtxyqzb06/2018-05-01_1 KSP.log.7z?dl=1

I would like to help but I have no where near the same mod count and I cant load your Gemini 3 craft due to differing mods. You do have a lot(810) of NullReferenceException for ClickThroughFix which probably not related to the problem at hand.

Spoiler

NullReferenceException: Object reference not set to an instance of an object
  at KSP.UI.Screens.EditorActionGroups.ConstructGroupActionList () [0x00000] in <filename unknown>:0 
  at KSP.UI.Screens.EditorActionGroups.ConstructGroupList () [0x00000] in <filename unknown>:0 
  at KSP.UI.Screens.EditorActionGroups.ClearSelection (Boolean reconstruct) [0x00000] in <filename unknown>:0 
  at ClickThroughFix.CBTMonitor.Update () [0x00000] in <filename unknown>:0 
 
(Filename:  Line: -1)

I did do a few quick drops of my own but nothing like that happened. 

You sure Valentina wasnt playing some head banging music.
